  "response": "Niacin, also known as Vitamin B3, is not typically added during the cultivation or processing of cannabis. However, it\u2019s important to note that cannabis plants naturally contain small amounts of niacin as part of their nutrient profile, as it is an essential nutrient for all plants.\n\nIn some cases, niacin or other vitamins might be included in certain cannabis-derived products (like edibles, tinctures, or topicals) for additional health benefits, but this would be specific to the product formulation and not a standard practice in cannabis cultivation or preparation.\n\nIf you\u2019re asking about a specific product or context, it would be best to check the product\u2019s ingredient list or consult the manufacturer for detailed information. Let me know if you\u2019d like more details!",
